Evocative and immersive. Every aspect of this  from the music, the beautiful artwork, the superlative voice acting to the truly sublime storytelling come together into something that transcends the mere gaming experience. This is genre defining and nothing short of a masterpiece. It not just sets the bar for click and point adventure games but i believe heralds a quiet and triumphant resurgence. The game's flow reminds me of another recent masterpiece "Life is Strange", but in my humble opinion it does much more with much less. Usually with the horror genre it is all too easy to overplay your hand and end up with kitsch. But Oxenfree maintains a steady hand on the throttle all throughout, never giving away too much or too little, with just enough out of reach to keep you going. And I could go on. The beautiful minimalist artwork, the absolutely gorgeous music. And the dialogue was so smooth and organic I genuinely kept getting sucked into the banter. My advice is to just play it. It's worth the small expenditure. I would rather pay lunch money to buy something this good than poor, hastily made freebgames that keep bombarding me with ads for poorer, even more annoying games every 3 seconds. Because God knows this level of workmanship needs encouraging. Great job guys.
